      "acceptanceCriteria": "The modelled QoI (normalised index of hemolysis, NIH) must map directly to the clinical endpoint; mapping must be validated against in-vivo or clinical reference data.",
      "rationale": "NIH is computed from the power-law hemolysis model and compared to in-vitro data, but no mapping to clinical in-vivo hemolysis endpoints is established. Achieved level 3 falls short of the required level 5."
    },
