      "acceptanceCriteria": "Independent simulation replication by a second analyst must confirm reproducibility of hemolysis index within stated uncertainty bounds.",
      "rationale": "No independent analyst replication has been performed. Single-analyst workflow without peer-check of boundary condition setup. Epistemic gap flagged at MRL 5."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Sensitivity of hemolysis predictions to turbulence model selection (SST k-ω vs. RSM) and hemolysis power-law exponent must be quantified; model-form uncertainty must be incorporated into total uncertainty budget.",
      "rationale": "Only SST k-ω turbulence closure was used; no turbulence model sensitivity study was conducted. Power-law exponent uncertainty was not propagated. Model-form uncertainty is entirely uncharacterised. Epistemic gap at MRL 5."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Probability distributions for all uncertain model inputs (viscosity, density, hemolysis model constants) must be defined and propagated through Monte Carlo UQ to produce hemolysis index confidence intervals.",
      "rationale": "Monte Carlo UQ was initiated but input probability distributions for hemolysis model constants C and α were assumed uniform without literature justification. Full propagation to output confidence intervals is incomplete. Epistemic gap."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "A minimum of three independent experimental replicates per operating point must be available with inter-replicate variability reported to support statistical comparison.",
      "rationale": "FDA pump dataset provides single-run data at most operating points; inter-replicate variability is not available. Statistical comparison between model and experiment is therefore not feasible. Epistemic gap at MRL 5."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Boundary conditions applied in the CFD model must be demonstrated to be equivalent to those measured in the validation experiment, including inlet velocity profile, outlet pressure, and rotational speed, within ±2%.",
      "rationale": "Inlet velocity profiles were approximated as uniform; no experimental LDV or PIV data were available to confirm inlet profile equivalency. Rotational speed equivalency was assumed but not verified against tachometer data. Epistemic gap."
